WEBVTT

00:02.540 --> 00:07.170
♪♪

00:07.170 --> 00:10.750
Meredith: Before surgery, we ask
patients a series of questions.

00:10.750 --> 00:12.540
"Do you have a job
to return to?

00:12.540 --> 00:14.580
Do you have a support system
at home?"

00:14.580 --> 00:17.380
We're screening
for mental illness.

00:17.380 --> 00:19.830
Anxiety, depression,
delusions.

00:19.830 --> 00:25.710
♪♪

00:25.710 --> 00:28.790
We need to make sure
you're of sound mind.

00:32.120 --> 00:34.580
We need to make sure
you know what to expect.

00:34.580 --> 00:38.920
♪♪

00:38.920 --> 00:41.920
But if we check patients
for mental illness,

00:41.920 --> 00:43.210
why not surgeons?

00:43.210 --> 00:46.460
[ Vomiting ]

00:46.460 --> 00:48.040
Someone should really
get on that.

00:50.830 --> 00:52.790
She's in the worst part
of the detox.

00:52.790 --> 00:54.880
I can stay stay, help...

00:54.880 --> 00:57.000
No, I'm okay. I got it.
Thank you, though.

00:57.000 --> 00:59.120
Okay. Well, good luck.
[ Betty coughs ]

00:59.120 --> 01:03.880
♪♪

01:03.880 --> 01:05.460
All right.
Dr. Webber, we have to go.

01:05.460 --> 01:07.620
Vik Roy and his lawyer brother
are here.

01:07.620 --> 01:09.620
What do you mean "we"?
You're the chief.

01:09.620 --> 01:10.830
And you fired him.

01:10.830 --> 01:12.000
They say how much
it would cost to settle?

01:12.000 --> 01:13.620
No, and unlike you,

01:13.620 --> 01:15.040
we don't have millions
of dollars at our disposal.

01:15.040 --> 01:16.920
And if we can't settle,

01:16.920 --> 01:20.420
we have to make sure we were
100% justified in firing him.

01:20.420 --> 01:23.290
I do recall his having
a disrespectful attitude

01:23.290 --> 01:25.210
toward a patient who tried
to cut off his own hand.

01:25.210 --> 01:26.790
Acted as if
it were a joke.

01:26.790 --> 01:28.380
Ooh, go on.

01:28.380 --> 01:30.290
Well, I called
Dr. Carina DeLuca

01:30.290 --> 01:31.790
to tell the boy
that masturbation

01:31.790 --> 01:33.170
was perfectly healthy --

01:33.170 --> 01:35.880
Stop. I want you to
imagine that sentence

01:35.880 --> 01:37.960
with "Your Honor"
at the end of it.

01:39.380 --> 01:41.040
Yeah, never mind.
Mm.

01:41.040 --> 01:44.460
Avery, do you have anything
helpful on Dr. Roy?

01:44.460 --> 01:46.620
I think I do. He tried to
take advantage of Dr. Kepner

01:46.620 --> 01:48.540
during a particularly
vulnerable time in her --

01:48.540 --> 01:51.330
"When he was an intern and she
was an attending, Your Honor."

01:51.330 --> 01:52.670
You know what?

01:52.670 --> 01:55.080
-Forget I...said anything.
-[ Exhales sharply ]

01:58.750 --> 02:00.040
Owen:
He spits up a lot.

02:00.040 --> 02:02.710
I thought it was GERD
or A pyloric stenosis, but --

02:02.710 --> 02:04.380
No, they just barf.

02:04.380 --> 02:06.620
I think it's triggered by
the cleanliness of your shirt.

02:06.620 --> 02:08.620
[ Chuckles ]
Oh. The babies.

02:08.620 --> 02:11.290
I love them like this,
Enjoy them like this.

02:11.290 --> 02:13.380
Hey you, um, why don't you go
get yourself checked in, okay?

02:15.210 --> 02:16.830
Sofia got suspended
from school.

02:16.830 --> 02:18.330
From second grade?!

02:18.330 --> 02:19.420
What, did she color
outside the lines?

02:19.420 --> 02:21.210
No, she stole
the field-trip money.

02:21.210 --> 02:22.460
What?
Oh, that'll do it.

02:22.460 --> 02:24.210
Why?
Why? Uh, 'cause
she's acting out.

02:24.210 --> 02:26.380
[ Chuckles ] 'Cause she's sad
'cause I'm a terrible mother.

02:26.380 --> 02:28.420
I don't know, but
enjoy those babies.

02:33.500 --> 02:35.000
Any minute now,
she's gonna realize

02:35.000 --> 02:36.500
I am the love
of her life.

02:36.500 --> 02:38.000
Meredith Grey
is straight.

02:38.000 --> 02:39.920
Ever heard her talk
about Cristina Yang?

02:39.920 --> 02:43.250
Hey. Someone needs to run
this bloodwork up to the lab.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.540
Hey! You know, we're also
shorthanded in the clinic today,

02:45.540 --> 02:47.460
and there is a nasty
hemorrhoid in bed seven

02:47.460 --> 02:49.040
that needs to be
lanced and drained.

02:49.040 --> 02:51.500
I've got the bloodwork!

02:51.500 --> 02:53.580
Have fun with
your hemorrhoid.

02:53.580 --> 02:55.500
I'd rather lance a hemorrhoid
than be a hemorrhoid.

02:55.500 --> 02:57.580
Great, then you got rectals
in the ICU after that.

02:57.580 --> 03:00.120
[ Sighs ]
You want bed sores
in geriatrics, too?

03:02.620 --> 03:06.420
Wish I could say it was nice
to see you back at work, but...

03:06.420 --> 03:08.080
Come on.

03:08.080 --> 03:09.960
I'm gonna show you
the coolest thing ever,

03:09.960 --> 03:12.580
on the tiniest patient ever.

03:12.580 --> 03:15.080
♪♪

03:20.830 --> 03:23.250
Don't assume
the worst, okay?

03:23.250 --> 03:26.000
The worst being my mom
is roaming the street
in her nightgown?

03:26.000 --> 03:29.040
Or my mom's dead and
nobody thought to tell me?

03:32.500 --> 03:34.250
[ Engine shuts off,
keys jingle ]

03:36.290 --> 03:37.880
[ Exhales sharply ]
Okay. I'm going.

03:37.880 --> 03:43.880
♪♪

03:45.000 --> 03:51.040
♪♪

03:52.170 --> 03:55.580
Mom?
It's me -- Alex!

03:55.580 --> 03:57.580
You there?!

03:59.830 --> 04:01.500
[ Doorknob rattling ]

04:01.500 --> 04:06.750
♪♪

04:06.750 --> 04:12.000
♪♪

04:12.000 --> 04:14.460
Looking for someone?

04:14.460 --> 04:16.500
Uh, yes. Uh...

04:16.500 --> 04:18.790
The lady that lives here.
Helen Karev?

04:18.790 --> 04:24.790
♪♪

04:28.710 --> 04:34.750
♪♪

04:38.380 --> 04:40.250
What happened?!
Is it bad?!

04:40.250 --> 04:41.710
Oh, my God --
Is it bad?!

04:41.710 --> 04:43.790
Who's the guy?! Did he --
Does he know where she is?!

04:43.790 --> 04:46.080
Yeah.

04:47.460 --> 04:49.330
She's at work.

04:49.330 --> 04:55.330
♪♪

05:01.960 --> 05:03.620
Meredith: I'll talk about that
in the presentation,

05:03.620 --> 05:05.420
but Dr. Wilson and I
are very encouraged

05:05.420 --> 05:06.880
by the work that we've done
so far.

05:06.880 --> 05:09.710
Was any of this work funded
by Harper Avery money?

05:09.710 --> 05:11.620
The Catherine Fox
Foundation. No.

05:11.620 --> 05:13.500
Do you feel renaming
the foundation is enough?

05:13.500 --> 05:15.000
But we haven't
simply renamed it.

05:15.000 --> 05:17.460
It's a whole new foundation
with a new direction,

05:17.460 --> 05:19.500
which will be exemplified
here at Grey Sloan.

05:19.500 --> 05:21.380
What do you have to say
to the dozens of women

05:21.380 --> 05:24.710
denied the opportunity to do
such research by Harper Avery?

05:24.710 --> 05:30.040
♪♪

05:30.040 --> 05:32.170
Dr. Grey?
I said, what do you --

05:32.170 --> 05:34.080
I couldn't be prouder

05:34.080 --> 05:36.040
of the work that my team
and I accomplished

05:36.040 --> 05:38.330
in the face of what seemed
to be insurmountable odds.

05:38.330 --> 05:39.920
If you'll excuse me,
I have work to do.

05:39.920 --> 05:42.500
Thanks so much.
Thank you. Excuse me.

05:42.500 --> 05:44.500
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Myers to Oncology.

05:44.500 --> 05:47.120
Dr. Myers to Oncology.

05:47.120 --> 05:49.080
What's her problem?
Tomophobia.

05:49.080 --> 05:51.290
Fear of medical
procedures.

05:51.290 --> 05:53.120
She equates surgery
with death.

05:53.120 --> 05:55.250
I've heard of patients
who have died

05:55.250 --> 05:56.710
because they
refuse treatment.

05:56.710 --> 05:58.920
Well, it's because of her dad.
He had an appendectomy.

05:58.920 --> 06:00.420
And they told him
it was nothing,

06:00.420 --> 06:01.880
and then there were
complications.

06:01.880 --> 06:04.040
He went in for surgery,
and then she...

06:04.040 --> 06:05.920
never saw him again.

06:05.920 --> 06:07.380
She was 5.

06:07.380 --> 06:08.960
What's DeLuca doing here?

06:08.960 --> 06:10.290
Oh, I brought him
to cheer him up.

06:10.290 --> 06:11.920
And so far,
it's depressing me more.

06:11.920 --> 06:13.750
Well, the exciting part
is the surgery, not the patient.

06:13.750 --> 06:15.380
You got a golden ticket.

06:15.380 --> 06:18.830
This is the spina bifida surgery
on an exteriorized uterus.

06:18.830 --> 06:21.250
Besides the Texas Children's
Fetal Center,

06:21.250 --> 06:23.250
we are one of the
only places to do this.

06:23.250 --> 06:27.960
Okay, people. Warm faces,
library voices, and lay terms.

06:27.960 --> 06:30.120
-[ Hushed voice ] Yay.
-[ Hushed voice ] Yay.

06:30.120 --> 06:32.670
Hi. Teresa and Ed.
How we doin'?

06:32.670 --> 06:34.330
Gettin' there.

06:34.330 --> 06:36.120
But could you go over
the whole thing one last time?

06:36.120 --> 06:37.460
-I think it helps.
-It does.

06:37.460 --> 06:39.500
It does. It helps me
to hear it out loud.

06:39.500 --> 06:41.380
Of course.
Um, DeLuca?

06:41.380 --> 06:44.460
Teresa Benson,
24 weeks pregnant,

06:44.460 --> 06:46.830
baby diagnosed with spina bifida
with meningocele.

06:46.830 --> 06:48.080
Lay terms.

06:48.080 --> 06:49.790
Right. Uh...

06:49.790 --> 06:52.710
Look, b-because your --
your baby has spina bifida,

06:52.710 --> 06:55.750
the tissue around her spinal
cord hasn't fully closed.

06:55.750 --> 06:57.790
And this can cause
problems after birth

06:57.790 --> 06:59.750
like, uh, paralysis,

06:59.750 --> 07:01.750
bowel and bladder problems,
fluid on the brain --

07:01.750 --> 07:04.250
Buh-buh-buh-buh!
But I will nip it in the bud.

07:04.250 --> 07:05.620
I'm gonna make
a really small incision,

07:05.620 --> 07:07.000
I'm gonna pull out
your uterus

07:07.000 --> 07:10.420
and use very tiny instruments
to repair the spinal defect,

07:10.420 --> 07:12.880
while she stays
very safely inside.

07:12.880 --> 07:14.670
Maggie: I'll give her
a little medication

07:14.670 --> 07:16.210
to keep her
perfectly still,

07:16.210 --> 07:19.040
and I will be there, monitoring
her heart the whole time.

07:19.040 --> 07:20.500
-Great.
-Okay.

07:20.500 --> 07:21.880
Okay. See?
It's kind of a miracle.

07:21.880 --> 07:23.250
Mm-hmm.
[ Chuckles ]

07:23.250 --> 07:25.120
You're gonna be under
general anesthesia.

07:25.120 --> 07:27.040
I'm gonna make
a little tiny incision --

07:27.040 --> 07:29.250
No! No, no! No.
God. Sorry.

07:29.250 --> 07:31.710
I...I can't. I'm sorry.
No, no. I ca--

07:31.710 --> 07:34.420
-I'm sorry. I can't.
-All right.

07:34.420 --> 07:37.170
Teresa, the chances of
something happening to you

07:37.170 --> 07:39.710
are so, so s--
Just knock me out.

07:39.710 --> 07:41.960
Just sneak up from behind me
when I'm leaving and sedate me.

07:41.960 --> 07:43.960
I can't, because
it's against the law.

07:43.960 --> 07:46.880
But I have a sedative, okay?
It'll be very, very quick.

07:46.880 --> 07:48.670
No! No, no, no, no, no!
Please take me home!

07:48.670 --> 07:50.500
-Please take me home!
-Okay, okay, okay. All right.

07:50.500 --> 07:51.960
Listen.
We can wait all day.

07:51.960 --> 07:53.670
We'll just --
We'll give you some time.

07:53.670 --> 07:55.580
And I can, uh, go check
some other patients.

07:55.580 --> 07:57.000
It's gonna be okay.

07:57.000 --> 07:58.920
[ Breathing sharply ]

07:58.920 --> 08:00.330
I'll give her therapist
a call.

08:00.330 --> 08:03.710
[ Sobbing ]

08:03.710 --> 08:06.170
[ Door opens ]

08:06.170 --> 08:08.120
[ Door closes ]

08:11.500 --> 08:16.710
♪♪

08:16.710 --> 08:22.210
♪♪

08:22.210 --> 08:24.790
I'll with you in one --
just in one s--

08:27.500 --> 08:28.960
Hey.

08:29.920 --> 08:32.580
Alex?

08:32.580 --> 08:35.000
Your neighbor said you
got your old job back,

08:35.000 --> 08:36.830
but I didn't think
that seemed possible.

08:39.040 --> 08:40.670
Alex.

08:43.170 --> 08:45.080
My God.

08:48.120 --> 08:50.330
I've missed you so much!

08:50.330 --> 08:51.920
[ Laughs, sobs ]

09:00.670 --> 09:02.620
[ Door bell jingles ]

09:02.620 --> 09:04.170
-Coffee. Black.
-You got it.

09:05.790 --> 09:07.750
-Not smart.
-Excuse me?

09:07.750 --> 09:09.120
The coffee's terrible.

09:09.120 --> 09:11.460
It requires copious amounts
of, uh, cream and sugar.

09:11.460 --> 09:13.210
Well, if it's good coffee
you're after,

09:13.210 --> 09:15.670
there's a great cart at the
hospital across the street.

09:15.670 --> 09:17.790
No, I like the light
in here.

09:17.790 --> 09:20.120
And the smell
of stale beer.

09:20.120 --> 09:21.880
It does make
a good hideout.

09:21.880 --> 09:26.330
♪♪

09:26.330 --> 09:28.670
You know what? You're right. Can
you pass me the cream, please?

09:30.380 --> 09:31.710
Thanks.

09:31.710 --> 09:34.080
Are you here for the
Meredith Grey presentation?

09:34.080 --> 09:36.380
Actually I...

09:36.380 --> 09:38.080
am.
Me too.

09:41.000 --> 09:42.670
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:42.670 --> 09:45.000
After much soul searching
on the part of my client...

09:45.000 --> 09:46.960
Bailey: "Brother."

09:46.960 --> 09:51.210
...he has arrived at a request
we think is more than generous.

09:51.210 --> 09:53.420
He is willing to return
to work immediately

09:53.420 --> 09:55.460
with pay for the weeks
he has missed,

09:55.460 --> 09:57.620
free medical expenses
for the accident,

09:57.620 --> 09:59.790
and...

09:59.790 --> 10:02.210
a formal apology...

10:02.210 --> 10:04.920
from the chief.

10:04.920 --> 10:09.540
[ Chuckles ] That sounds
more than reasonable.

10:09.540 --> 10:12.380
We'll take that under
advisement. Thank you
for your time.

10:15.960 --> 10:17.540
[ Chuckles ]
[ Door slams ]

10:17.540 --> 10:20.920
♪♪

10:22.830 --> 10:24.790
[ Gasps ]

10:29.170 --> 10:32.170
The nightmares will stop.
I promise.

10:35.670 --> 10:38.580
A day into my last detox,
I was afraid I was gonna die.

10:40.080 --> 10:42.460
The next day,
I was afraid I wasn't.

10:42.460 --> 10:45.380
You just got to keep telling
yourself it is not forever.

10:45.380 --> 10:46.880
Your life must be
really pathetic

10:46.880 --> 10:48.380
for you to just
have all this time

10:48.380 --> 10:49.880
to sit here
watching me puke.

10:55.500 --> 10:57.710
Don't ignore me.

10:57.710 --> 11:00.000
I'm not ignoring you.

11:00.000 --> 11:01.580
I'm ignoring the demon.

11:01.580 --> 11:03.330
What demon?

11:03.330 --> 11:04.710
Your last high.

11:04.710 --> 11:06.710
It is like a demon,

11:06.710 --> 11:08.750
and it is dying
a painful death right now.

11:08.750 --> 11:10.080
And it knows it's dying,

11:10.080 --> 11:12.670
so it's trying to push me away
so that it can live.

11:12.670 --> 11:15.460
But I am the exorcist.
I'm protected.

11:15.460 --> 11:18.670
So the demon can say
whatever it wants. I'm good.

11:18.670 --> 11:20.830
Pathetic.

11:23.040 --> 11:24.580
None of the doctors
are really sure.

11:24.580 --> 11:28.380
Just sometimes, with age,
schizophrenia burns itself out.

11:28.380 --> 11:29.880
But that doesn't mean
you're cured.

11:29.880 --> 11:31.380
No, no.

11:31.380 --> 11:34.170
But it's --

11:34.170 --> 11:37.040
It's more like the
volume's been turned down.

11:37.040 --> 11:38.750
Medications have
a better effect.

11:38.750 --> 11:42.000
And, uh, I just have to be
really vigilant with my routine.

11:42.000 --> 11:43.460
Routine?

11:43.460 --> 11:45.170
Yeah. I-I, uh...

11:45.170 --> 11:46.710
I keep my days the same.

11:46.710 --> 11:48.330
I-I make my tea
at the same time,

11:48.330 --> 11:50.420
I take my breaks
at the same time.

11:50.420 --> 11:53.920
It just helps keep
reality more tangible.

11:53.920 --> 11:55.710
Oh. Thank you, Joyce.

11:55.710 --> 11:56.790
Thanks, Helen.

12:00.920 --> 12:02.330
So you're fine?

12:02.330 --> 12:05.620
You're just --
You're fine now?

12:05.620 --> 12:07.500
You didn't tell me?

12:07.500 --> 12:10.620
You just -- You just
stopped cashing the checks.

12:10.620 --> 12:14.580
Well, you're so busy.
Uh, you deserve your space.

12:14.580 --> 12:16.210
-I didn't -- I didn't wa--
-My space?!

12:16.210 --> 12:18.540
You're my mom.

12:18.540 --> 12:21.460
I came here because
I was worried about you.

12:21.460 --> 12:23.540
Why didn't you tell me
you were doing better?

12:23.540 --> 12:26.750
Why didn't you tell me that?
I had so much to manage.

12:26.750 --> 12:29.960
Manage? I'm not something
you manage. I am your son.

12:29.960 --> 12:31.580
I think you need to go.

12:31.580 --> 12:34.040
What?
Look, I realize
you were worried.

12:34.040 --> 12:36.580
And I'm sorry I caused that.
But right --

12:36.580 --> 12:38.620
But right now I have to
take care of myself.

12:38.620 --> 12:40.500
I'm -- I'm...
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:40.500 --> 12:42.000
I'm getting really upset,

12:42.000 --> 12:45.170
and, uh --
and in moments like this,

12:45.170 --> 12:47.210
I need --
I need to keep my focus,

12:47.210 --> 12:50.540
and I'm at work,
so I need to do that.

12:50.540 --> 12:53.040
Please.

12:56.880 --> 12:58.330
[ Door slams ]

12:58.330 --> 12:59.670
What happened?

12:59.670 --> 13:02.170
My presence is upsetting her.
She asked me to go.

13:02.170 --> 13:04.500
-What? What'd you do?
-I didn't do anything!

13:04.500 --> 13:06.710
I mean -- [Scoffs ]
She's my mom.

13:06.710 --> 13:09.250
I came all the way out here.
I thought she was dead.

13:09.250 --> 13:11.710
Okay, let's --
let's get out of here.

13:11.710 --> 13:14.710
-And go where?
-Just...somewhere else.

13:14.710 --> 13:16.380
How much money was it?

13:16.380 --> 13:20.000
Um, 30 times $40,
so not exactly grand theft

13:20.000 --> 13:21.210
but enough
to make me feel like

13:21.210 --> 13:22.960
I've fundamentally failed
as a parent.

13:22.960 --> 13:25.960
No. Every kid steals
something at some point.

13:25.960 --> 13:27.670
I stole a lipstick
from the drug store.

13:27.670 --> 13:29.250
Not quite $1,200, but --

13:29.250 --> 13:30.580
So, what did your dad do
when he found out?

13:30.580 --> 13:33.040
He never knew.
I was an excellent thief.

13:33.040 --> 13:35.620
Maggie: Teresa.
Teresa, wait!

13:35.620 --> 13:37.670
Hey. Whoa!
What's -- What's going on?

13:37.670 --> 13:39.580
She's checking out.
She consented to sedation,

13:39.580 --> 13:41.290
but when we tried
to get the IV in --

13:41.290 --> 13:43.080
I'm sorry.
I-I will come back.

13:43.080 --> 13:44.710
I'll -- I'll try
to come back.

13:44.710 --> 13:45.920
C-Can you please
tell her?

13:45.920 --> 13:47.960
Teresa, if you don't have

13:47.960 --> 13:49.750
this procedure today,
then your baby could be --

13:49.750 --> 13:51.330
I know!
She can be paralyzed!

13:51.330 --> 13:54.000
Please don't say that
anymore!

13:54.000 --> 13:56.120
[ Exhales sharply ]
Is that everything?

13:56.120 --> 13:59.290
Can we go?
Ed? Please.

13:59.290 --> 14:01.920
Okay. All right.

14:01.920 --> 14:06.290
♪♪

14:13.540 --> 14:14.750
[ Sighs ]
Bailey.

14:14.750 --> 14:17.080
All the boy wants
is an apology.

14:17.080 --> 14:19.750
Do you know how much worse
this could be?

14:19.750 --> 14:22.750
You know, I am a big believer
in the power of words

14:22.750 --> 14:24.250
and an even bigger
believer

14:24.250 --> 14:26.290
in the power
of a good apology.

14:26.290 --> 14:27.670
[ Breathes sharply ]

14:27.670 --> 14:30.790
But I will not sully my belief
in those two things

14:30.790 --> 14:35.210
by putting fake words
into some forced apology

14:35.210 --> 14:37.210
to a person
who is in the wrong!

14:37.210 --> 14:40.580
Roy made a mistake,
a grave one.

14:40.580 --> 14:44.960
But it's -- it's possible
I overcorrected in firing him.

14:44.960 --> 14:46.420
You did no such thing!

14:46.420 --> 14:47.620
If he had operated
under the con--

14:47.620 --> 14:49.330
But he didn't.

14:49.330 --> 14:51.830
But you know who has
operated in this hospital

14:51.830 --> 14:55.120
knowingly
under the influence?

14:55.120 --> 14:56.250
Me.

14:58.080 --> 15:00.420
You gonna fire me, too?

15:00.420 --> 15:02.210
Now, that's
just manipulative.

15:02.210 --> 15:04.000
This has nothing
to do with you.

15:04.000 --> 15:07.670
♪♪

15:07.670 --> 15:10.380
[ Sighs ]

15:10.380 --> 15:12.580
Thought you had
a big surgery today.

15:12.580 --> 15:14.170
Oh, it was canceled.

15:14.170 --> 15:15.880
[ Voice breaking ]
Cold feet.

15:15.880 --> 15:18.830
-Are you okay?
-[ Sniffles ]

15:18.830 --> 15:20.500
[ Sobs softly ]

15:20.500 --> 15:22.250
Sofia stole the money

15:22.250 --> 15:24.500
so that she could buy
a plane ticket to New York.

15:24.500 --> 15:27.580
And she didn't want
to tell me

15:27.580 --> 15:29.210
because she --

15:29.210 --> 15:30.620
'cause she didn't want
to hurt my feelings.

15:30.620 --> 15:31.790
[ Sniffles ]

15:31.790 --> 15:33.000
She said that?

15:33.000 --> 15:34.500
No.

15:34.500 --> 15:37.460
I read it in her diary.
I picked the stupid lock.

15:37.460 --> 15:41.000
Which...is also another
gold-star parenting moment.

15:41.000 --> 15:43.330
[ Chuckles softly ]

15:43.330 --> 15:45.040
What are you gonna do?

15:45.040 --> 15:47.710
[ Sniffles ]

15:47.710 --> 15:50.540
I don't know.

15:50.540 --> 15:53.750
Because I can't keep her
against her will, can I?

15:53.750 --> 15:55.330
You're her mom.

15:55.330 --> 15:57.710
You can do whatever
you think is best for her.

16:00.500 --> 16:02.540
Oh.

16:02.540 --> 16:04.420
Where are you going?

16:04.420 --> 16:07.290
♪♪

16:07.290 --> 16:09.250
♪ I came home last night ♪

16:09.250 --> 16:10.880
So, are you
in Seattle much?

16:10.880 --> 16:12.460
All the time.

16:12.460 --> 16:15.580
I like it. It's so gloomy
and, you know, rainy.

16:15.580 --> 16:17.170
You like the gloom?

16:17.170 --> 16:18.580
Well, I grew up
in Los Angeles,

16:18.580 --> 16:21.330
so I'm way over my sunshine
quota. I like the rain.

16:21.330 --> 16:23.960
Meredith: Well, I didn't know
anybody grew up in Los Angeles.

16:23.960 --> 16:25.420
I thought everyone
just moved there

16:25.420 --> 16:27.750
to chase their dreams
and then have them crushed.

16:27.750 --> 16:30.580
No, some people, uh, grow their
crushed dreams right there.

16:30.580 --> 16:33.380
-No offense.
-No, none taken.

16:33.380 --> 16:36.040
It's weird -- Everyone that
likes it already lives there.

16:36.040 --> 16:38.790
Everyone else
seems to hate it.

16:38.790 --> 16:40.080
Something stronger?

16:40.080 --> 16:42.250
Oh, not for me. I have a thing.
Thanks, Mark.

16:42.250 --> 16:44.460
I'll make a fresh pot,
Dr. Grey.

16:44.460 --> 16:46.880
"Dr. Grey."

16:46.880 --> 16:48.420
[ Chuckles ]

16:48.420 --> 16:50.290
You're kidding me.
[ Chuckling ]

16:50.290 --> 16:51.830
You could've said that.

16:51.830 --> 16:53.120
-I could've.
-Tha--

16:53.120 --> 16:54.750
I knew --
Is everything okay?

16:54.750 --> 16:56.500
[ Laughs ]

16:56.500 --> 16:58.790
It's just -- No.
Of course -- I mean --

16:58.790 --> 17:00.540
Yeah, you're --
you're Dr. Grey,

17:00.540 --> 17:02.580
and of course
you're terrific.

17:02.580 --> 17:07.380
And that just makes it really
hard to keep hating you.

17:07.380 --> 17:08.960
Why would you hate me?

17:08.960 --> 17:11.040
Because you wasted
a year of my life.

17:11.040 --> 17:13.790
♪ Yes, I do ♪

17:13.790 --> 17:15.830
[ Knocking on door ]

17:20.620 --> 17:23.040
You're at my house.
Wh-- Is that normal?

17:23.040 --> 17:24.420
Is that --
Is that a thing you do?

17:24.420 --> 17:26.290
No. It's not normal.
It's really weird.

17:26.290 --> 17:28.330
I just -- I needed to
ask you a question.

17:29.960 --> 17:31.790
If it weren't you
having surgery,

17:31.790 --> 17:34.250
if it was your daughter's
life at stake --

17:34.250 --> 17:37.170
and she was -- and she was
standing right there,
and she needed surgery...

17:37.170 --> 17:39.250
what would you do?

17:39.250 --> 17:42.210
Would you let her
have it?

17:42.210 --> 17:44.750
♪ There is a
swelling storm ♪

17:44.750 --> 17:46.960
Can I come in?

17:46.960 --> 17:52.040
♪ And I'm caught up in
the middle of it all ♪

17:53.920 --> 17:56.880
♪ And it takes control ♪

17:56.880 --> 17:58.080
This is dumb.

17:58.080 --> 17:59.500
So let it be dumb.

17:59.500 --> 18:01.920
♪ Of the person
that I thought I was ♪

18:01.920 --> 18:06.420
♪ The boy I used to know ♪

18:06.420 --> 18:10.960
♪ But there is a light
in the dark ♪

18:10.960 --> 18:13.920
♪ Why can't I hold on? ♪

18:16.000 --> 18:20.290
♪ It comes and goes
in waves ♪

18:20.290 --> 18:21.960
♪ Into the flood ♪

18:21.960 --> 18:24.710
[ Pitching machine whirring ]

18:24.710 --> 18:28.170
♪ Into the flood ♪

18:28.170 --> 18:30.330
She ruined
my whole damn life.

18:30.330 --> 18:32.420
I hid Aaron and Amber
from her.

18:32.420 --> 18:34.540
♪ A feeling I thought
was set in stone ♪

18:34.540 --> 18:36.500
Failed Geometry
'cause that was the year

18:36.500 --> 18:38.540
that she decided to get up
and walk out of the house

18:38.540 --> 18:39.880
every morning --

18:39.880 --> 18:42.710
no shoes, no money,
nothing.

18:42.710 --> 18:44.500
[ Bat hits ball ]

18:44.500 --> 18:46.670
I'd spend all of first period
looking for her,

18:46.670 --> 18:49.330
and there's she'd be,
just laughing her ass off,

18:49.330 --> 18:51.830
or yelling at nobody
on the street corner.

18:51.830 --> 18:53.120
[ Bat hits ball ]

18:55.500 --> 18:57.210
No friends,
no girlfriends,

18:57.210 --> 18:58.920
'cause, I mean, who the hell
wants to hang out

18:58.920 --> 19:01.750
with the freak
with the psycho for a mom?

19:01.750 --> 19:04.000
But it's good
that she's better, right?

19:04.000 --> 19:07.250
Yeah, yeah. Sure.
It's -- It's freaking great.

19:07.250 --> 19:09.420
She's nice.
She's -- She's calm.

19:09.420 --> 19:11.880
She's -- She's working,
and she's eating,

19:11.880 --> 19:14.000
and she's looking
perfectly normal

19:14.000 --> 19:15.670
in her perfectly
normal life!

19:15.670 --> 19:17.580
Okay, if she's good,
why are you so angry?

19:17.580 --> 19:19.460
Why the hell now?!

19:19.460 --> 19:20.790
[ Bat clattering ]

19:20.790 --> 19:22.380
Now?! Why now?!

19:22.380 --> 19:24.120
Now, when --
when nobody needs her,

19:24.120 --> 19:26.330
when nobody
wants her around,

19:26.330 --> 19:28.170
w-when Aaron and Amber
don't need a mother

19:28.170 --> 19:29.710
instead of me
raising them?!

19:29.710 --> 19:32.380
Why, when all the
freaking damage is done?!

19:32.380 --> 19:36.540
Now she's good?
She's fine?! She's okay?!

19:36.540 --> 19:39.330
[ Scoffs ] And I can't even
say a damn thing about it.

19:39.330 --> 19:42.920
Because I have been cleaning up
her mess my whole damn life.

19:42.920 --> 19:46.580
But never once did I cause it.
And I am not about to start now!

19:46.580 --> 19:48.920
♪ It always does ♪

19:48.920 --> 19:50.120
You want to
take a break?

19:50.120 --> 19:53.040
-No. Load it, please.
-Okay.

19:53.040 --> 19:55.170
[ Coin rattles ]
♪ And carries us away ♪

20:02.170 --> 20:03.620
[ Sighs ]

20:03.620 --> 20:08.250
I just know that if you put me
under, I won't come back.

20:08.250 --> 20:10.830
That I'll die.
That I'll never see my baby.

20:10.830 --> 20:13.000
That I'll never see Ed.
I'll never come back.

20:15.380 --> 20:17.500
I used to roller-skate.

20:17.500 --> 20:19.540
Uh...

20:19.540 --> 20:22.790
M-My family used to move around
a lot, which was really scary.

20:22.790 --> 20:24.500
But whenever
we'd get somewhere new,

20:24.500 --> 20:26.080
first thing,
my dad would...

20:26.080 --> 20:28.080
my dad would
take me skating.

20:28.080 --> 20:29.960
And so no matter
where I was in the world,

20:29.960 --> 20:31.830
that would stay the same.

20:31.830 --> 20:33.420
And I -- I felt safe.

20:33.420 --> 20:35.120
[ Inhales deeply ]

20:35.120 --> 20:38.420
I did it in college, um,
and I did it in med school,

20:38.420 --> 20:40.330
and then I did it when
I first got my job here.

20:40.330 --> 20:41.670
Um, I worked with kids,

20:41.670 --> 20:45.040
and so it kind of
made them feel safe, too.

20:45.040 --> 20:47.960
And then I was
in an accident.

20:47.960 --> 20:50.420
And they told me that...

20:50.420 --> 20:52.460
that I may lose my leg.

20:52.460 --> 20:55.170
And all I could
think about was...

20:55.170 --> 20:56.880
I'll never be able
to skate again.

20:56.880 --> 20:58.790
[ Sobs softly ]

20:58.790 --> 21:00.330
And a lot of my life
would change,

21:00.330 --> 21:05.420
but that seemingly tiny thing
felt like...

21:05.420 --> 21:08.620
I felt like my whole life
was being taken away from me.

21:08.620 --> 21:11.420
And that all the stuff
that my dad had given me,

21:11.420 --> 21:13.120
you know, all the magic
and all the safety,

21:13.120 --> 21:15.460
was just gonna be gone.

21:15.460 --> 21:19.500
And so I made my wife
promise me

21:19.500 --> 21:21.210
that she would not
let them take my leg.

21:21.210 --> 21:23.830
No...matter...what.

21:26.330 --> 21:29.080
But then it came down
to my life or my leg.

21:29.080 --> 21:33.210
And they needed her consent
to amputate.

21:34.670 --> 21:39.830
I am so lucky...

21:39.830 --> 21:43.040
that she and my doctors could
clearly see what I couldn't.

21:43.040 --> 21:44.750
And you know what?

21:44.750 --> 21:47.710
I skated again.

21:47.710 --> 21:51.380
And my worst fear
was wrong.

21:51.380 --> 21:53.330
And the only thing I really lost
was my leg.

21:53.330 --> 21:55.540
And I would've died
if I'd have kept it.

21:55.540 --> 21:59.000
And I have so much joy
in my life right now.

21:59.000 --> 22:00.460
More than I could
possibly imagine.

22:00.460 --> 22:02.290
I have a --
I have a healthy daughter,

22:02.290 --> 22:04.790
and I have work that I love,
and I'm okay.

22:04.790 --> 22:07.830
I'm -- I'm great.

22:07.830 --> 22:09.250
And I want that for you.

22:09.250 --> 22:11.000
I want that
for your life, too.

22:11.000 --> 22:12.750
[ Whimpers ]
I just -- I...

22:12.750 --> 22:13.830
[ Sobbing ] I'll die.

22:13.830 --> 22:15.380
No.

22:17.750 --> 22:19.960
Your dad died.

22:19.960 --> 22:21.580
And it was unfair.
It was terrible.

22:21.580 --> 22:23.460
And it still scares you.
[ Sobbing ]

22:23.460 --> 22:25.710
But you're a mom now.
You're her mom.

22:25.710 --> 22:28.960
And you need to do
what's best for her.

22:28.960 --> 22:34.960
♪♪

22:36.880 --> 22:39.250
Hey.
Hey.

22:39.250 --> 22:40.880
Everything okay?

22:40.880 --> 22:43.920
A surgery I was excited about
got canceled.

22:43.920 --> 22:45.420
What about you?

22:45.420 --> 22:47.670
Oh, I spent all day
cutting checks.

22:47.670 --> 22:49.790
Paid $38 million
before lunch.

22:49.790 --> 22:52.250
I took a break to read
a hard-hitting op-ed titled

22:52.250 --> 22:55.080
"Too Little Too Late: How Much
Did Grandbaby Avery Know?"

22:55.080 --> 22:57.500
Yeah.
Good stuff.

22:57.500 --> 22:59.120
Well, it's easy,
and it's lazy

22:59.120 --> 23:01.120
to sit outside
a complicated situation

23:01.120 --> 23:03.920
and attack
the people involved.

23:03.920 --> 23:05.380
But you know what's sexy?

23:05.380 --> 23:06.500
What's that?

23:06.500 --> 23:08.580
The way you just
keep doing you.

23:08.580 --> 23:10.330
Is that right?
Mm-hmm.

23:10.330 --> 23:12.880
You want to go find
someplace private?

23:12.880 --> 23:14.290
Yep.

23:14.290 --> 23:16.500
Take your mind off money?
Mm-hmm.

23:16.500 --> 23:18.960
You know, if we keep doing this
every time I write big checks,

23:18.960 --> 23:21.330
then we're not gonna
get much work done.

23:21.330 --> 23:23.170
I'm okay with that.

23:23.170 --> 23:26.670
♪♪

23:26.670 --> 23:28.540
Hey, Betty?

23:28.540 --> 23:31.250
Sounds like it's
quieted down in there.

23:31.250 --> 23:33.000
I know you hate
my guts right now.

23:33.000 --> 23:35.540
But will you let me change
your fluids? It'll really help.

23:37.120 --> 23:38.830
Come on, Betty.
We'll play a game.

23:38.830 --> 23:42.290
I will just sit there, and you
can mean-girl me until I cry.

23:44.380 --> 23:46.960
Betty? You okay?

23:46.960 --> 23:48.750
[ Doorknob rattles ]

23:48.750 --> 23:51.670
Betty?! Betty!

23:51.670 --> 23:56.580
♪♪

23:56.580 --> 24:02.120
♪♪

24:02.120 --> 24:04.880
David: So, I went to
my team, and I said,

24:04.880 --> 24:06.620
"I have good news
and bad news.

24:06.620 --> 24:08.500
The good news --

24:08.500 --> 24:10.710
the abdominal-wall transplant
definitely works.

24:10.710 --> 24:12.000
Bad news?

24:12.000 --> 24:14.040
We can all go home. Meredith
Grey just pulled it off."

24:14.040 --> 24:16.750
[ Chuckles ] I fail to see
how that warrants hatred.

24:16.750 --> 24:18.290
I had no idea.

24:18.290 --> 24:19.540
And I'm sure your work

24:19.540 --> 24:21.460
will help perfect the process
in the future.

24:21.460 --> 24:22.830
You ever hear
of Pete Conrad?

24:22.830 --> 24:23.830
No. Is he a surgeon?

24:23.830 --> 24:25.880
Astronaut.
Oh.

24:25.880 --> 24:28.540
First guy to walk on the Moon
during the second Moon landing.

24:28.540 --> 24:31.380
And one of only 12 people
in history to do that.

24:31.380 --> 24:33.710
And no one cares.
Because he wasn't first.

24:33.710 --> 24:35.040
You looking for
an apology?

24:35.040 --> 24:36.420
You're barking up
the wrong tree,

24:36.420 --> 24:38.750
because I won
fair and square.

24:38.750 --> 24:40.040
That's just another
reason I hate you.

24:40.040 --> 24:41.420
Get in line.

24:42.750 --> 24:44.330
Beat someone else
to the punch?

24:44.330 --> 24:45.960
Uh...

24:45.960 --> 24:47.880
Someone tried
to steal mini-livers.

24:47.880 --> 24:49.710
A friend.
Or so I thought.

24:49.710 --> 24:52.920
Literally to my face said
she was going to steal it

24:52.920 --> 24:54.210
and beat me to market.

24:54.210 --> 24:55.330
Sounds like
there's a story there.

24:55.330 --> 24:56.580
There is.

24:58.290 --> 25:00.830
So...got any -- [ Chuckles ]
Got any pets?

25:03.620 --> 25:05.880
That doesn't make sense. She
texted me she was coming here.

25:05.880 --> 25:07.880
So if she's not here,
she's not okay!

25:07.880 --> 25:09.380
I'm sorry,
but we haven't seen Teresa

25:09.380 --> 25:10.750
since you left
this morning.

25:10.750 --> 25:12.380
She's here.

25:12.380 --> 25:16.210
Babe, what happened,
what are you --

25:16.210 --> 25:18.210
[ Moaning softly ]

25:18.210 --> 25:19.750
-We had -- It's okay.
-[ Groans ]

25:19.750 --> 25:22.290
We had a little trouble
getting out of the car.

25:22.290 --> 25:25.580
And then we had a little trouble
getting in the door.

25:25.580 --> 25:30.170
But we're here. So those are
some little victories.

25:30.170 --> 25:33.040
-Mm-hmm.
-We're gonna keep going, okay?

25:33.040 --> 25:34.880
We're just
gonna keep going.

25:34.880 --> 25:39.120
♪♪

25:39.120 --> 25:40.580
[ Coin rattles ]

25:40.580 --> 25:42.380
[ Can thudding ]

25:46.420 --> 25:48.500
Sorry me and my family
is so depressing.

25:48.500 --> 25:50.290
Shut up.

25:50.290 --> 25:53.710
She had one really good year
when I was a kid.

25:53.710 --> 25:55.040
She worked at that library,

25:55.040 --> 25:57.420
and I would hang out
with her there.

25:57.420 --> 25:59.120
We'd play hide-and-seek
in the stacks.

25:59.120 --> 26:01.000
[ Chuckles softly ]

26:01.000 --> 26:04.710
My whole life, all I ever wanted
was a mom who wasn't sick.

26:04.710 --> 26:08.960
I didn't care about
toys or sports

26:08.960 --> 26:12.670
or any of that crap.

26:12.670 --> 26:16.080
I just wanted a mom
who was okay.

26:16.080 --> 26:18.000
And she is.

26:18.000 --> 26:20.120
She finally is.

26:20.120 --> 26:22.460
[ Pitching machine whirs,
bat hits ball ]

26:22.460 --> 26:24.120
And she doesn't
want me there.

26:26.790 --> 26:29.420
You may never hear what you
want to hear from your mom.

26:29.420 --> 26:31.500
You may never
get an acknowledgment.

26:31.500 --> 26:33.540
You may never get
an apology.

26:33.540 --> 26:35.330
But you have a shot
at having a mom.

26:35.330 --> 26:38.000
And that --
Alex, that's --

26:38.000 --> 26:40.580
That's something
that's real.

26:44.790 --> 26:46.830
Arizona: Okay, it's just sleep.
It's not dying.

26:46.830 --> 26:48.830
You're gonna go to sleep,
and then you're gonna wake up.

26:48.830 --> 26:50.250
And you'll be okay.

26:50.250 --> 26:51.960
[ Exhales sharply ]
You promise?

26:53.710 --> 26:55.170
I promise.

26:55.170 --> 26:57.500
Easy for you to say.

26:57.500 --> 27:00.960
If you're wrong, you're off
the hook, 'cause I'll be dead.

27:00.960 --> 27:03.580
[ Chuckles ]
I promise.

27:03.580 --> 27:08.120
♪♪

27:14.330 --> 27:15.750
Don't be nervous,
Dr. Schmitt.

27:15.750 --> 27:17.540
I'll be talking with
all of your colleagues.

27:17.540 --> 27:18.960
And for the moment,

27:18.960 --> 27:20.830
these conversations
are off the record.

27:20.830 --> 27:23.080
-Okay.
-Okay?

27:23.080 --> 27:27.000
So, how would you describe
your experience

27:27.000 --> 27:28.960
working with
Dr. Vikram Roy?

27:28.960 --> 27:31.500
Especially any mistakes

27:31.500 --> 27:34.790
or...gross incompetence

27:34.790 --> 27:36.540
you may have witnessed.

27:36.540 --> 27:37.920
If you're asking

27:37.920 --> 27:40.540
if I think you made the
wrong decision firing him,

27:40.540 --> 27:42.080
I don't.

27:42.080 --> 27:43.920
It was the right call.

27:43.920 --> 27:46.920
If the Chief of Surgery
can admit to being high,

27:46.920 --> 27:48.290
so should an intern.

27:48.290 --> 27:50.380
And I watched you.
[ Chuckles ]

27:50.380 --> 27:52.210
I watched you
stare into the abyss

27:52.210 --> 27:54.000
of a patient you'd opened up,

27:54.000 --> 27:57.620
higher than a kite,
for what felt like an eternity.

27:57.620 --> 27:59.290
But you made the right call.

27:59.290 --> 28:03.290
That is leadership,
on drugs or not.

28:03.290 --> 28:05.420
"Your Honor."

28:08.500 --> 28:09.960
Hey. Got your page.
What's up?

28:09.960 --> 28:11.790
Hey.

28:11.790 --> 28:16.620
Uh, well, this was what I was
able to set aside for Harriet.

28:16.620 --> 28:19.250
Everything I have
might be up for grabs,

28:19.250 --> 28:20.580
but they can't touch this.

28:20.580 --> 28:22.120
Thank you.

28:22.120 --> 28:24.000
Yeah, she's gonna be okay.

28:24.000 --> 28:26.380
Everything else
is fair game? Really?

28:26.380 --> 28:29.250
Well, the foundation has to
keep the hospitals afloat,

28:29.250 --> 28:32.000
so I have decided to pay all
the personal settlements myself.

28:32.000 --> 28:35.250
People must
really appreciate that.

28:35.250 --> 28:37.380
[ Chuckles softly ]
It's mixed.

28:37.380 --> 28:40.380
You know, a lot of folks want
jobs, others want lost wages.

28:40.380 --> 28:42.250
Of course, there's
a few lawyers out for blood.

28:42.250 --> 28:46.040
But, I mean, it's really hard
to quantify loss like this.

28:46.040 --> 28:48.040
This means a lot.

28:48.040 --> 28:49.710
And it will to her
one day, too.

28:49.710 --> 28:51.040
[ Chuckles softly ]

28:54.580 --> 28:57.040
So, you know, there's this
story in the Bible.
Oh, yeah?

28:57.040 --> 28:59.080
Yeah, hear me out. Hear me out.
You're gonna like this one.

28:59.080 --> 29:02.120
About this rich young ruler
who wants to follow Jesus.

29:02.120 --> 29:05.460
And Jesus tells him to
sell all of his belongings

29:05.460 --> 29:07.500
and give the money
to the poor.

29:07.500 --> 29:11.170
So for what it's worth,
you are on a really good path.

29:13.750 --> 29:15.830
Your buddy Jesus interested
in buying a yacht?

29:15.830 --> 29:17.120
[ Laughs ]

29:19.620 --> 29:21.250
So my mother had
a choice to make --

29:21.250 --> 29:23.210
follow the medicine,
or her friend.

29:23.210 --> 29:25.830
-Tough choice.
-It isn't, though.

29:25.830 --> 29:28.290
You follow your friend.
Period.

29:28.290 --> 29:29.880
And my mother didn't.

29:29.880 --> 29:31.920
And Marie got the short end
of the stick.

29:31.920 --> 29:34.670
So in her mind, it's okay
to stab me in the back.

29:34.670 --> 29:36.080
But it's totally not.

29:36.080 --> 29:38.170
It's totally not.
And I can't even look at her.

29:38.170 --> 29:40.120
But you still feel for her.

29:40.120 --> 29:42.540
Which pisses me off
even more.

29:42.540 --> 29:45.880
Because I won fair and square.
And screw her.

29:47.750 --> 29:51.250
But something terrible
happened to her.

29:51.250 --> 29:53.540
But that doesn't justify
what she did.

29:53.540 --> 29:57.710
I saw your mom speak once,
on the Grey Method, ages ago.

29:57.710 --> 30:00.670
Most inspiring presentation
of my career.

30:00.670 --> 30:03.250
It made me switch
from plastics to general.

30:03.250 --> 30:04.880
Really?

30:04.880 --> 30:06.500
See? That's the thing.

30:06.500 --> 30:08.710
I mean, she was hell
to live with,

30:08.710 --> 30:13.750
but she really did inspire
so many people...

30:13.750 --> 30:18.170
and inspired a whole generation
of female surgeons.

30:18.170 --> 30:20.000
That's --
That's the dream.

30:22.080 --> 30:23.710
That's the dream.

30:23.710 --> 30:25.460
That's why we do
what we do, right?

30:25.460 --> 30:28.460
I mean, everybody wants
their place in history.

30:28.460 --> 30:32.210
Nobody wants to be the astronaut
that no one remembers.

30:32.210 --> 30:34.920
-Are you trying to rub it in?
-Sorry. No, no, no.

30:34.920 --> 30:38.040
But that's what she took
from Cerone.

30:38.040 --> 30:40.250
She stole the dream.

30:40.250 --> 30:42.420
And that's why Cerone feels

30:42.420 --> 30:43.960
that she deserves
that place in history.

30:43.960 --> 30:45.420
Because she does.

30:51.380 --> 30:55.040
♪ Hollow one ♪

30:55.040 --> 30:58.250
♪ With inverted tongue ♪

30:58.250 --> 31:00.210
[ Monitor beeping ]

31:00.210 --> 31:05.960
♪ From whence
does fulfillment come? ♪

31:07.920 --> 31:11.880
♪ When I expel ♪

31:11.880 --> 31:14.420
♪ From this mortal shell ♪

31:14.420 --> 31:17.120
[ Liquid suctioning ]

31:17.120 --> 31:22.750
♪ Will I die for living numb? ♪

31:24.920 --> 31:29.000
♪ Am I vital ♪

31:29.000 --> 31:32.960
♪ If my heart is idle? ♪

31:32.960 --> 31:39.000
♪ Am I doomed? ♪

31:41.880 --> 31:46.000
♪ Am I vital ♪

31:46.000 --> 31:50.040
♪ If my heart is idle? ♪

31:50.040 --> 31:56.040
♪ Am I doomed? ♪

31:58.620 --> 32:02.620
♪ I feel you ♪

32:02.620 --> 32:06.580
♪ But nobody else ♪

32:06.580 --> 32:12.580
♪ Though you're someone
I can't see ♪

32:15.380 --> 32:19.250
♪ Yet you say nothing ♪

32:19.250 --> 32:22.330
Alex, please.
This is for the best.

32:24.880 --> 32:26.750
Look. I don't want
to mess with your routine.

32:26.750 --> 32:28.750
I, uh -- I just needed
to say a couple things.

32:32.620 --> 32:34.790
I want a library card.

32:34.790 --> 32:36.790
What?
I mean, it's...

32:36.790 --> 32:40.460
You have to be here for your
job. That's part of it, right?

32:40.460 --> 32:43.170
♪ Will you cast me ♪

32:43.170 --> 32:47.330
♪ To the wayside? ♪

32:48.670 --> 32:51.420
♪ Well, I feel the peeling ♪

32:51.420 --> 32:55.330
I'm so happy for you.
And proud.

32:55.330 --> 32:59.210
And, uh, seeing you here
doing so well, it...

32:59.210 --> 33:00.710
it was a lot.

33:00.710 --> 33:03.380
And I got mad. And...

33:03.380 --> 33:05.540
And I know it was
a lot for you, too.

33:05.540 --> 33:08.120
So much more.

33:08.120 --> 33:10.000
♪ Am I vital ♪

33:10.000 --> 33:11.460
And I know...

33:11.460 --> 33:14.120
♪ If my heart is idle? ♪

33:14.120 --> 33:18.000
I know that I haven't
stayed in touch.

33:18.000 --> 33:21.460
But I always thought
about you.

33:21.460 --> 33:23.580
And I'm...

33:23.580 --> 33:26.830
I'm so happy.

33:26.830 --> 33:28.920
I'm really happy for you.

33:28.920 --> 33:31.540
♪ So I can see ♪

33:31.540 --> 33:33.540
♪ If I'm doomed ♪

33:33.540 --> 33:36.710
Um...

33:36.710 --> 33:38.420
Uh, I'm gonna go.

33:38.420 --> 33:40.120
You want to do the stamp?

33:40.120 --> 33:41.960
Huh?
The due-date stamp.

33:41.960 --> 33:44.330
I always change it at the end
of the night for tomorrow.

33:44.330 --> 33:46.790
And when you were
a little boy,

33:46.790 --> 33:48.920
you used to love
to do that for me.

33:51.580 --> 33:52.880
[ Laughs ]

33:52.880 --> 33:54.580
It's silly. Never mind.

33:54.580 --> 33:57.040
No, no.
No, no, no.

33:57.040 --> 33:58.040
That'd be cool.

33:58.040 --> 33:59.750
Yeah?
Yeah.

33:59.750 --> 34:02.920
♪ So I can see ♪

34:02.920 --> 34:04.420
[ Chuckles ]

34:04.420 --> 34:06.920
-[ Laughs ]
-These things are archaic now.

34:06.920 --> 34:09.290
♪♪

34:17.540 --> 34:19.330
[ Applause ]

34:25.000 --> 34:26.500
Thank you all for coming.

34:29.710 --> 34:34.330
Before I get started, I have
a statement I'd like to make.

34:34.330 --> 34:36.710
My mother, Ellis Grey,

34:36.710 --> 34:38.960
did not come up with
the Grey Method on her own.

34:38.960 --> 34:41.330
[ Attendees murmuring ]

34:41.330 --> 34:45.830
She did it with the help of
and alongside Dr. Marie Cerone.

34:45.830 --> 34:48.580
Due to the reprehensible
behavior of Harper Avery,

34:48.580 --> 34:50.710
Marie Cerone was blacklisted.

34:50.710 --> 34:53.500
And my mother made
the regrettable decision

34:53.500 --> 34:56.170
to publish the work
as her own.

34:56.170 --> 34:58.290
I'd like to think
that was a result

34:58.290 --> 35:00.380
of the time
or the workplace culture,

35:00.380 --> 35:02.420
but that I can't know.

35:02.420 --> 35:05.000
What I can do...

35:05.000 --> 35:07.380
is correct that error.

35:08.960 --> 35:10.540
So from this day forward,

35:10.540 --> 35:14.540
I would like the method
known as the Grey Method

35:14.540 --> 35:17.580
to be known
as the Grey-Cerone Method.

35:17.580 --> 35:20.580
[ Applause ]

35:20.580 --> 35:26.580
♪♪

35:30.420 --> 35:32.960
And now on to business...

35:32.960 --> 35:34.540
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

35:34.540 --> 35:36.620
The Formation
of New Liver Tissue

35:36.620 --> 35:40.380
with Intraperitoneal
Hepatocyte Injection.

35:40.380 --> 35:42.880
Dr. Wilson and I
are faced with a problem...

35:42.880 --> 35:45.040
And she's okay?
My baby's okay?

35:45.040 --> 35:47.580
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
I got a good look at her.

35:47.580 --> 35:50.880
She's better than fine. She's
got two super-strong legs.

35:50.880 --> 35:52.670
And a-a great
head of hair.

35:52.670 --> 35:55.460
And a closed spine.
We like that, too.

35:55.460 --> 35:57.250
I can't believe I put you all
through that.

35:57.250 --> 35:59.540
I was so scared --
for nothing.

35:59.540 --> 36:03.170
Hey. Would you stop it?
You saved our little girl, babe.

36:03.170 --> 36:05.000
You're my hero.

36:05.000 --> 36:07.750
Arizona:
He's right. You did.

36:07.750 --> 36:09.380
You did it.

36:09.380 --> 36:11.040
You did everything
that you could for her.

36:11.040 --> 36:13.290
I'm a mom.

36:13.290 --> 36:15.250
You are a mom.

36:15.250 --> 36:16.670
[ Chuckles softly ]

36:20.580 --> 36:25.500
Dr. Roy, on behalf of
Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital,

36:25.500 --> 36:29.120
I would like to tell you
that I am s--

36:29.120 --> 36:31.460
I...

36:31.460 --> 36:32.880
I...

36:32.880 --> 36:36.710
[ Breathes deeply ]

36:36.710 --> 36:40.210
Um, I think what Chief Bailey
is trying to say

36:40.210 --> 36:41.670
is that she would like --

36:41.670 --> 36:44.960
I would like to tell you...

36:44.960 --> 36:48.580
that you are lucky.

36:48.580 --> 36:54.420
Lucky to learn from good doctors
who have given everything

36:54.420 --> 36:58.830
in the face of obstacles
you cannot begin to imagine.

36:58.830 --> 37:03.790
People that fought and bled
to pave a way.

37:03.790 --> 37:06.920
Doctors like me.

37:06.920 --> 37:09.710
And I have made mistakes,

37:09.710 --> 37:11.670
but firing you
was not one of them.

37:11.670 --> 37:14.790
You got what you deserve.

37:14.790 --> 37:17.170
That said...

37:17.170 --> 37:20.960
I am willing to have you back

37:20.960 --> 37:24.580
for a one-year
probationary period,

37:24.580 --> 37:28.460
during which time
I will watch you like a hawk.

37:28.460 --> 37:30.920
I've spent the better
part of a year

37:30.920 --> 37:34.460
researching the best way
to get up in someone's butt,

37:34.460 --> 37:38.290
so expect to find me
up yours.

37:38.290 --> 37:42.540
And if...
if you don't screw it up,

37:42.540 --> 37:46.210
I will shape you
into an amazing surgeon.

37:52.250 --> 37:53.620
I accept your apology.

37:57.040 --> 37:59.120
Meredith: Fixing your mental
health isn't like surgery.

37:59.120 --> 38:00.830
Write that up.

38:00.830 --> 38:03.330
We can't just run the bloodwork
and check the vitals.

38:03.330 --> 38:05.500
A doctor got her high
for the first time.

38:05.500 --> 38:07.880
It wasn't a dealer.

38:07.880 --> 38:09.210
It wasn't some random pusher
from the street.

38:09.210 --> 38:13.380
It was a surgeon.
Like me.

38:13.380 --> 38:15.960
And I took an oath
to do no harm.

38:15.960 --> 38:18.380
And I just feel like
there's this epidemic
going on out there.

38:18.380 --> 38:20.000
There are these kids...

38:20.000 --> 38:23.420
They're good kids with ruined
lives and ruined families.

38:23.420 --> 38:24.830
And it's all because

38:24.830 --> 38:27.830
somebody like me
who didn't know any better --

38:27.830 --> 38:32.500
somebody like me who doesn't
understand addiction --

38:32.500 --> 38:37.040
wrote a prescription
in an attempt to help.

38:37.040 --> 38:38.500
And the hilarious part is

38:38.500 --> 38:43.040
I'm so angry about it all
that I am craving drugs!

38:43.040 --> 38:45.830
With mental health, progress
is way harder to measure.

38:45.830 --> 38:48.170
I just hope she comes back.

38:48.170 --> 38:51.880
And if something's wrong,
we have to take action.

38:51.880 --> 38:54.170
Owen: You know you're the
first girl I've introduced
to my mom in 20 years?

38:54.170 --> 38:55.830
Seriously?
I'm really, really nervous.

38:55.830 --> 38:57.210
Why would you say that?

38:57.210 --> 38:58.960
Oh, come on.
She's gonna love you.

38:58.960 --> 39:03.120
Oh. Hey. Uh, Mom,
this is my fiancée, Jo.

39:03.120 --> 39:06.880
Ohh.
Lovely to meet you.

39:06.880 --> 39:09.210
You too, Ms. Karev.

39:09.210 --> 39:14.170
♪♪

39:14.170 --> 39:15.880
Uh, we're getting
married soon,

39:15.880 --> 39:18.380
and we would love for you
to come to the wedding.

39:18.380 --> 39:21.170
Wow. Nothing would
make me happier.

39:21.170 --> 39:23.710
[ Chuckles ]

39:23.710 --> 39:28.500
But, uh, travel's tough for me
to manage with my routine.

39:28.500 --> 39:30.380
We totally get it.

39:30.380 --> 39:33.330
There's a lot of uncertainty.

39:33.330 --> 39:37.380
There's a lot of fear.

39:37.380 --> 39:39.710
And what might be easy
for one person...

39:39.710 --> 39:41.250
for someone else might take

39:41.250 --> 39:43.210
inner strength
you can't even imagine.

39:43.210 --> 39:45.420
That's my ride.

39:45.420 --> 39:47.210
Right on time.

39:47.210 --> 39:49.330
Yeah. We got
a plane to catch.

39:51.080 --> 39:53.330
My sweetest boy.

39:53.330 --> 39:55.580
♪♪

39:55.580 --> 39:57.620
My truest love.

39:57.620 --> 40:01.000
♪♪

40:01.000 --> 40:02.960
But we have to try.

40:02.960 --> 40:06.750
♪♪

40:06.750 --> 40:08.420
[ Bus door closes ]

40:08.420 --> 40:14.420
♪♪

40:16.830 --> 40:19.170
Marie: Mer Mer.

40:21.080 --> 40:23.540
Thank you so much.

40:23.540 --> 40:25.080
Can we talk?

40:25.080 --> 40:27.620
Marie, I think I've said
all there is to say.

40:30.540 --> 40:32.880
We have to stand up
to our demons.

40:32.880 --> 40:34.500
♪ That's privilege ♪

40:34.500 --> 40:36.330
We have to face reality
whenever possible

40:36.330 --> 40:38.460
and ask for help
when we can't.

40:38.460 --> 40:40.420
I know that you don't
agree with me.

40:40.420 --> 40:42.710
I know -- I know that
you think that I coddle her,

40:42.710 --> 40:43.920
but I'm her mother.

40:43.920 --> 40:45.620
And I have to do what's best
for her if I can,

40:45.620 --> 40:47.080
and in this case, I can.

40:47.080 --> 40:48.830
Okay, then,
why defend yourself to me

40:48.830 --> 40:50.380
if you don't even care
what I think?

40:50.380 --> 40:53.000
♪ Can't sleep at night ♪

40:53.000 --> 40:55.290
♪ Can't convince myself ♪

40:55.290 --> 40:57.620
♪ To turn it off ♪

40:57.620 --> 40:59.580
♪ To let go ♪

40:59.580 --> 41:03.500
[ Voice breaking ] I just wish
that what's best for her

41:03.500 --> 41:06.210
wasn't what's
worst for me.

41:06.210 --> 41:11.500
♪ War ♪

41:11.500 --> 41:13.080
♪ Am I runnin' late? ♪

41:13.080 --> 41:15.500
♪ I get overwhelmed ♪

41:15.500 --> 41:17.500
♪ All the awful dreams ♪

41:17.500 --> 41:19.670
♪ All the bright screens ♪

41:19.670 --> 41:21.540
♪ Is my lover there? ♪

41:21.540 --> 41:23.790
♪ Are we breakin' up? ♪

41:23.790 --> 41:25.670
♪ Did she find someone else? ♪

41:25.670 --> 41:30.880
♪ And leave me alone? ♪

41:30.880 --> 41:36.880
♪ Alone ♪

41:39.040 --> 41:43.420
♪♪

41:43.420 --> 41:45.460
[ Phone ringing, click ]

41:45.460 --> 41:47.250
Callie, hey.

41:47.250 --> 41:51.040
Um, so, I was --
I was thinking.

41:51.040 --> 41:54.500
Um, and I think --
I think that...

41:54.500 --> 41:57.250
I think that Sofia should move
back to New York with you.

41:57.250 --> 42:00.250
And when we do that,
healing is possible.

42:00.250 --> 42:02.290
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

42:07.330 --> 42:10.790
And I think I need
to move back with her.

42:10.790 --> 42:16.330
♪♪

42:26.000 --> 42:32.000
♪♪

42:34.460 --> 42:40.460
♪♪

42:42.670 --> 42:48.710
♪♪
